# contour: loop=1 with NO gate or trigger patched. Manual (contour.md 146):
# "when loop is on, the envelope will immediately start again once it has
# finished. It also starts without triggering. This converts contour into a
# kind of fancy LFO." With the gate permanently low, decay/sustain are never
# entered (manual 141): the cycle is attack -> release -> restart.
# tickrate 100. attack=1 -> 10 ticks; release=0.05 -> 10 ticks; decay patched
# to prove it is skipped (buggy behavior would decay to sustain 0.5 and hang).
# Cycle: attack t0..t10 (0 -> 1), release t10..t20 (1 -> 0), idle tick t20,
# restart at t21.
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[contour]
    loop    = 1
    attack  = 1
    decay   = 0.05
    release = 0.05
    output  = O1
>>>
@0 expect O1 0 tol 1e-4
@5 expect O1 0.5 tol 1e-4
@10 expect O1 1.0 tol 1e-4
@15 expect O1 0.5 tol 1e-4
@20 expect O1 0 tol 1e-4
@21 expect O1 0 tol 1e-4
@26 expect O1 0.5 tol 1e-4
@31 expect O1 1.0 tol 1e-4
@41 expect O1 0 tol 1e-4
